revision.text:
The term '''behest loan''' refers to a [[loan]] granted to individuals or corporations favored by a powerful government official despite their lack of qualifications to receive such a loan.  It is a mechanism for graft and [[political corruption]] particularly used in [[Authoritarian regime|authoritarian regimes]], where financial institutions such as banks are placed under intense pressure to approve such loans "at the behest" of high officials.<ref name="Araneta20060420">{{Cite news |url=https://www.philstar.com/headlines/2006/04/20/332342/pcgg-uncovers-130-behest-loans-worth-p50-billion |title=PCGG uncovers 130 behest loans worth P50 billion |last=Araneta |first=Sandy |date=2006-04-20 |work=The Philippine Star |access-date=2018-04-22}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.rappler.com/business/251-anatomy-of-a-behest-loan |title=Anatomy of a 'behest' loan |work=Rappler |access-date=2018-04-22 |language=en}}</ref>  The term has historically been most associated with the [[cronies]] of former Philippine president [[Ferdinand Marcos]],<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://business.inquirer.net/243711/three-decade-old-behest-loans |title=Three-decade old behest loans |last=Palabrica |first=Raul J. |access-date=2018-04-22 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=http://newsinfo.inquirer.net/951265/3-pnb-execs-to-be-tried-for-behest-loans |title=3 PNB execs to be tried for behest loans |last=Nonato |first=Vince F. |access-date=2018-04-22 |language=en}}</ref><ref name="Mogato20160224">{{Cite news |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-philippines-marcos/philippines-still-seeks-1-billion-in-marcos-wealth-30-years-after-his-ouster-idUSKCN0VX0U5 |title=Philippines still seeks $1 billion in Marcos wealth 30 years after... |last=Mogato |first=Manuel |date=2016-02-24 |work=U.S. |access-date=2018-04-22 |language=en-US}}</ref> although other officials have also been accused of engaging in the practice. <ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.manilatimes.net/speaker-smells-p5-6b-dbp-behest-loans/327497/ |title=Speaker smells P5.6B in DBP behest loans - The Manila Times Online |access-date=2018-04-22 |language=en-US}}</ref>

