{{Infobox animal | name = K9 Killer | image = | image_upright = | caption = | birth_name = | othername = | species = [[Canis lupus familiaris]] | breed = [[Malinois (Belgian Shepherd Dog)|Belgian Malinois]] | gender = Male | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | nationality = | occupation = [[anti-poaching]] work | employer = | role = | years_active = | known = | tricks = | awards = [[PDSA Gold Medal]] | title = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | owner =Amos Mzimba | residence = | parents = | children = | weight = | height = | appearance = | namedafter = | website = }} '''K9 Killer''' is a [[Malinois (Belgian Shepherd Dog)|Belgian Malinois]] dog who works with the [[Kruger National Park]]'s Special Operations Team to prevent [[rhinoceros]] poachers in [[South Africa]]. On 6 January 2016, the dog was awarded a [[PDSA Gold Medal]] for his anti-poaching work.<ref>{{Cite web | url = https://www.pdsa.org.uk/press-office/latest-news/2016/01/06/pdsa-gold-medal-k9killer | title = Supreme honour for South Africa’s most successful poacher-hunting dog | accessdate = 10 January 2016 | publisher = PDSA | date = 7 January 2016 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20160129213143/https://www.pdsa.org.uk/press-office/latest-news/2016/01/06/pdsa-gold-medal-k9killer | archivedate = 29 January 2016 | df = }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Smith|first1=Sam|title=South Africa's K9 Killer receives highest PDSA honour for saving rhino|url=http://traveller24.news24.com/Explore/Bush/south-africas-k9-killer-receives-highest-pdsa-honour-for-saving-rhino-20160113|website=Traveller24|publisher=News24|accessdate=13 January 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Grant|first1=Katie|title=K9 Killer: Dog receives PDSA Gold Medal for helping to save rhino from extinction|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/africa/k9-killer-dog-receives-pdsa-gold-medal-for-helping-to-save-rhino-from-extinction-a6801611.html|website=The Independent|publisher=The Independent}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.environment.gov.za/mediarelease/molewa_highlightsprogress_againstrhinopoaching|title=Minister Edna Molewa highlights progress in the fight against rhino poaching|last=|first=|date=2016-01-21|website=environmental affairs|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=2018-10-16}}</ref> Amos Mizmba is the owner of K9 Killer.<ref name=":2">{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-35264270|title=Rhino poacher- hunting dog from South Africa gets hero medal}}</ref>
== Breed background == The [[Malinois dog|Belgian Malinois]], a working class dog, can be employed for personal protection and scent tracking. They must receive [[Obedience training|training]] so they can channel their high energy drive tasks that their owners have given them. When Belgian Malinois are young, they require a lot of stimuli from their surroundings so that they can get used to them as they grow older.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.malinoisclub.com/abmc/about-malinois/faqs/|title=FAQs – ABMC|website=www.malinoisclub.com|language=en-US|access-date=2018-10-25}}</ref>
The Belgian Malinois <ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vetstreet.com/dogs/belgian-malinois#overview|title=Belgian Malinois Breed Information|work=Vetstreet|access-date=2018-11-14|language=en-US}}</ref>is a Belgian herding breed that originated from a small town in Belgium called Malines. The other name for a Belgian Malinois is the Chien de Berger (bair-zhai) Belge (belzh). This lively and energetic breed can be family friendly with the proper training and care. It can suffer from health problems, like most other breeds. Retinal atrophy, hip/elbow dysplasia, etc. Because of its energy an intelligence, the breed was enlisted in World War I.
== Origins == K9 Killer's lineage can be followed to the [[Iraq War|Iraq war]] and the [[Belgian Police|Belgian Police.]] His father had parents that served for the [[United States]] in the [[Iraq War]]. His mother was bred from two Belgian police dogs and was entered into an exchange program and sent to [[South Africa|South Africa.]]<ref name=":1">{{Cite news|url=https://lowvelder.co.za/203575/dog-trainer-testifies-killer-court/|title=Dog trainer testifies about Killer in court {{!}} Lowvelder|date=2014-06-27|work=Lowvelder|access-date=2018-10-19|language=en-US}}</ref>
== Canines duties in Kruger National Park == In [[Kruger National Park]] canines are being used in the tracking and apprehension of [[Poaching|poachers]]. This work includes scent detection of [[Firearm|firearms]] and [[Wildlife trade|illegal animal parts]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.defenceweb.co.za/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=47283:anti-poaching-dogs-a-game-changer-for-kruger&catid=87:border-security|title=Anti-poaching dogs a game-changer for Kruger {{!}} defenceWeb|last=Martin|first=Guy|website=www.defenceweb.co.za|language=en-gb|access-date=2018-10-19}}</ref> Once [[Suspect|suspects]] have been detected in the park, K9 Killer is loaded into a [[helicopter]] and flown to a drop off location.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-35264270|title=Poacher-hunting dog gets hero medal|date=2016|work=BBC News|access-date=2018-10-21|language=en-GB}}</ref> As of the last 4 years K9 Killer has led to the arrest of 115 poachers in Kruger National Park's.<ref name=":2" /> In order for K9 Killer to remain on the scent trails of humans he had to be introduced to the scents of [[Animal|animals]] in [[Kruger National Park]] at a young age. This 2-year training program [[Desensitization (medicine)|desensitized]] K9 Killer to the smells of animals.<ref name=":1" />
Kruger National Park<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-35264270|title=Poacher-hunting dog gets hero medal|date=2016|work=BBC News|access-date=2018-11-14|language=en-GB}}</ref>, in South Africa, suffers from rhinoceros poaching every year. Rhinoceros poaching has “increased from 13 poached rhinos in 2007 to 1,215 in 2014” (BBC News). Kruger National Park, however, has enlisted the help of a special Belgian Malinois, Killer. Alongside Killer's handler, Amos Mzimba, Killer has aided in the arrests of more than 115 rhinoceros poachers illegally hunting within the park grounds.
== Awards == The [[PDSA Gold Medal]] was awarded to K9 Killer in January 2016 for his fight against [[Poaching|anti-poaching]] in [[South Africa]]. Through the protection of human and non-human life, pets must show dedication to their duties in order to receive this honor.{{cn|date=October 2018}}
